        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 5:19PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 519 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dayton, or 8 miles southeast of Virginia City, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Carson City, Dayton, Dayton Valley Airpark, Rawe Peak, and Junction
U.S 50 And NV 341.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
